WorldStage Newsonline– Nestlé Nigeria Plc which is into manufacturing, marketing and distribution of food products including purified water and exports some of its products to other countries within and outside Africa, has released its annual report and financial statements for year ended 31 December 2020 with 1% growth in revenue to N287.084 billion from N284.035 billion in 2019. Profit for the year dropped by 14% to N39.212 billion from N45.683 billion in 2019. Despite the drop in profit, the company has declared N55.486 billion, a 10% increased from N50.334 billion in 2019. According to the company, “the directors propose a final dividend of N35.50, (N24.50k from the profit after tax for the year ended 31 December 2020, N5.00 and N6.00 from the after tax retained earnings for the year ended 31 December 2019 and 31 December 2018 respectively (2019:N45.00) per share on the issued share capital of 792,656,252 (2019:792,656,252) ordinary shares of 50k each, subject to approval by the shareholders at the Annual General Meeting.”